24/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Russian Ambassador to Macedonia Agaron Astatur said in an interview for MIA on Tuesday (23 September) that his country wants to convene an international conference on the Balkans. 
Astatur added that the UN, EU, United States and Russia should take part in it to guarantee a lasting peace in Southeast Europe. 
He urged that special attention be paid to the status of ethnic minorities and their rights. 
(MIA - 23/09/03)
